
Syrahs from Around the World
Tuesday, November 21
7:35PM - 8:10PM
Room C330

The world's best Syrah (aka Shiraz) wines come from three places on earth:
France's Rhone Valley, Southern Australia and California. Taste four wines
that show what this tasty grape is all about. Lesley Keffer will pour and
explain.

RSVP to: keffer@haas.berkeley.edu
Space limited
If we are overbooked, respondents will be chosen with Excell Crystal Ball.



Lesley Keffer
Evening MBA 2002
Haas School of Business
UC Berkeley
St. Supery Winery
